              <th class="border border-[#e5e5e5] px-4 py-3 text-left text-[#333] font-semibold">Primary Application</th>
              <th class="border border-[#e5e5e5] px-4 py-3 text-left text-[#333] font-semibold">Why It Fits</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td class="border border-[#e5e5e5] px-4 py-3 font-medium">LSTM</td><td class="border border-[#e5e5e5] px-4 py-3">Load forecasting, energy prediction</td><td class="border border-[#e5e5e5] px-4 py-3">Captures long-range temporal dependencies</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-[#fafbfc]"><td class="border border-[#e5e5e5] px-4 py-3 font-medium">CNN</td><td class="border border-[#e5e5e5] px-4 py-3">Fault detection, spatial patterns</td><td class="border border-[#e5e5e5] px-4 py-3">Identifies spatial features in sensor networks</td></tr>
            <tr><td class="border border-[#e5e5e5] px-4 py-3 font-medium">Reinforcement Learning</td><td class="border border-[#e5e5e5] px-4 py-3">Optimal control, real-time setpoints</td><td class="border border-[#e5e5e5] px-4 py-3">Learns control policies through trial and error</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-[#fafbfc]"><td class="border border-[#e5e5e5] px-4 py-3 font-medium">Gradient Boosting</td><td class="border border-[#e5e5e5] px-4 py-3">Anomaly detection, baselines</td><td class="border border-[#e5e5e5] px-4 py-3">Strong interpretability for tabular sensor data</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <p>These techniques enable enhanced load forecasting, fault detection, optimal power flow, and demand response methods that go well beyond what conventional PID loops and schedule-based control can achieve. The models do not replace domain expertise — they amplify it by processing more data, faster, and identifying patterns invisible in trend logs.</p>

